                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/76.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Hermosillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 13. Governor Riveros informs me that there is no doubt about
                    the Navolato Sugar Refineries being returned to their original owners, the
                    Almadas, some time before the capture of Culiacan and that Mr. Nelson Rhodes
                    Jr., who is at present in the United States can give the Department full
                    particulars regarding the same.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hostetter</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
